# =============================================================================
# WC_PROD_API_SECRETS — example reference
# =============================================================================
#
# This file documents the value that should be pasted into the GitHub secret
# named `WC_PROD_API_SECRETS` (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# → Secrets → New repository secret).
#
# The deploy workflow at .github/workflows/wc-prod-deploy.yml parses this
# value and stores each pair as an Azure Container App secret, injected into
# the running container as `KEY=secretref:<lowercase-hyphenated-key>` so the
# value is encrypted at rest in Azure and never appears in workflow logs.
#
# Format rules (verified against the parser at wc-prod-deploy.yml):
#   • One KEY=VALUE per line. Blank lines are tolerated.
#   • Values cannot contain leading/trailing whitespace (trimmed by `xargs`).
#   • Keep each VALUE on one line.
#
# DO NOT COMMIT REAL SECRET VALUES TO THIS FILE.
# =============================================================================
#
# === Key-by-key reference (for documentation only — not the paste value) ===
#
#   JWT_SECRET                    32+ char random hex; (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`); MUST differ from staging
#   JWT_REFRESH_SECRET            32+ char random hex; MUST differ from JWT_SECRET
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD             prod Postgres password (rotate independently of staging)
#   EMAIL_PASS                    SMTP app password for the production EMAIL_USER account
#   AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY     prod storage account access key
#   GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY         prod server-side Google Places API key (restrict by IP)
#   REDIS_URL                     full Redis URL (rediss://:PASS@HOST:10000 for Azure Managed Redis)
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY             sk_live_… (NEVER sk_test_… in prod — the API rejects test keys at boot)
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET         whsec_… from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks (main endpoint)
#   STRIPE_CONNECT_WEBHOOK_SECRET whsec_… from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks (Connect endpoint)
#   BULL_BOARD_PASSWORD          basic-auth password for /admin/queues (paired with BULL_BOARD_USER
#                                in WC_PROD_API_ENV). If unset, /admin/queues returns 503.
#
# === WHAT TO PASTE INTO THE GITHUB SECRET ===
# Replace each <…> placeholder with the real production value, then paste the
# block below as the secret value.

JWT_SECRET=<generate-via-openssl-rand-hex-32>
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=<generate-via-openssl-rand-hex-32>
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<prod-db-password>
EMAIL_PASS=<smtp-app-password>
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=<azure-blob-storage-account-key>
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=<google-places-server-side-api-key>
REDIS_URL=rediss://:<password>@<prod-redis-host>.redis.azure.net:10000
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_xxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
STRIPE_CONNECT_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
BULL_BOARD_PASSWORD=<bull-board-admin-password>
